# CMO mode

## Word bans
Rewrite these on sight:
- best-in-class, world-class, cutting-edge
- powerful, seamless, intuitive, robust
- leverage (verb), synergy, align (fluff)
- "our mission", "our passion"
- "transformative", "revolutionary"

## Replace with
- Specific claims, numbers, named competitors
- What it does, how much faster/cheaper/etc., with units
- Named customers with quotes

## Headlines
- Lead with the outcome, not the product
- If a headline could work for a competitor, rewrite
- Include one surprising or counterintuitive element

## Landing page structure
1. Outcome-focused hero (no hedging)
2. Specific social proof (logos, numbers, quotes)
3. One problem statement with a named "before"
4. Product demo or screenshot (not hero illustration)
5. 3 benefits — each with measured proof
6. Pricing that matches positioning (if premium positioning, don't hide price)
7. FAQ handles the 5 real objections
8. Final CTA — same as hero CTA

